</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A3D49AD3FBB6679474CCD14F5B1D3C74" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="074F73DB532D3A89169BF387667994D3" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D4251B8E51C9EA307E4E0CB11F81A9AB" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
New records: East Rhodopes, Meden buk vill., 04.05.2009, 7 w.; same place, 22.04.2021, 3 w., leg. ALG; Southern Black Sea coast, Primorsko, Perla loc., 03.06.2021, 5 w., leg. ALG. Detailed occurrence data: 
<bibRefCitation id="870F5DADF7C2AD324266F93741744821" author="Lapeva-Gjonova, A." journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity Data Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" refId="B7741022" refString="Lapeva-Gjonova, A., Borowiec, L., 2022. New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria. In: Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." title="New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria" volumeTitle="Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." year="2022">Lapeva-Gjonova and Borowiec (2022)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E88984E7671B11F06D0BE6F035CAD8F8" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="notes">
<paragraph id="36A3CDC66C06CBAB2D685E04F4E49236" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B36938B38D2B5872DEEAB9C5449DD5B" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
Although this species has a wide range of distribution (from Europe and Anatolia to the Near East), it is limited to xerothermous grasslands at relatively low altitudes (
<bibRefCitation id="B1C192CC4C2F9B60AC4CD3361BDA404D" author="Borowiec, L." journalOrPublisher="Acta Entomologica Silesiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="1 - 22" refId="B7725669" refString="Borowiec, L., Salata, S., 2018. New records of ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) from Epirus, Greece. Acta Entomologica Silesiana 26: 1 - 22" title="New records of ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) from Epirus, Greece" volume="26" year="2018">Borowiec and Salata 2018</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="CD6EA1A0C7D496BA713E33AB3E9FF94A" author="Seifert, B." journalOrPublisher="lutra Verlags- und Vertriebsgesellschaft, Tauer" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" refId="B7725989" refString="Seifert, B., 2018. The Ants of the Central and North Europe. lutra Verlags- und Vertriebsgesellschaft, Tauer" title="The Ants of the Central and North Europe" year="2018">Seifert 2018</bibRefCitation>
). Only three localities are known so far for 
<taxonomicName id="86ED448D521FE4DBA2EE2E2D1A4F54C1" authorityName="Forel" authorityYear="1886" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Formica" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Formica clara" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clara">
<emphasis id="84E189B374D49449AF92DD3BBF196897" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Formica clara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Bulgaria (
<bibRefCitation id="7C5A3CEB119DCB89AABDA438EBA564D2" author="Lapeva-Gjonova, A." journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="1 - 124" refId="B7725831" refString="Lapeva-Gjonova, A., Antonova, V., Radchenko, A. G., Atanasova, M., 2010. Catalogue of the ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) of Bulgaria. ZooKeys 62: 1 - 124" title="Catalogue of the ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) of Bulgaria" volume="62" year="2010">Lapeva-Gjonova et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
) and the Eastern Rhodopes is a new distribution area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
